useMemo is a React Hook used to cache (memorize) the result of an expensive calculation so it doesn't run on every render. 
const memoizedValue = useMemo(() => { return expensiveCalculation(); }, [dependency]); 
const total = useMemo(() => count * 2, [count]); 
useMemo remembers a calculated value and recalculates it only when needed.

useCallback is a React Hook used to cache (memorize) a function so React doesn't create a new function on every render. 
const memoizedFunction = useCallback(() => { // function code }, [dependency]); // 
const addToCart = useCallback((product) => { dispatch(addProduct(product)); }, []); 
Or // 
const handleClick = useCallback(() => { console.log("clicked"); }, []); 
useCallback remembers a function and recreates it only when needed.

The Shadow DOM is a special DOM that is isolated from the main DOM. It is mainly used in:
- Web Components
- Custom Elements
- UI Libraries
It helps prevent CSS and JavaScript conflicts. Why Shadow DOM? Imagine your website has: button { background: red; } But a third-party component wants: button { background: blue; } Without Shadow DOM, styles can conflict. With Shadow DOM, the component's styles stay isolated. Shadow DOM Example

```html
<custom-button></custom-button>
```
JavaScript:

```javascript
const shadow =
element.attachShadow({ mode: "open" });
shadow.innerHTML = `
<style>
button {
background: blue;
color: white;
}
</style>
<button>Buy Now</button>
`;
```
The styles inside the Shadow DOM won't affect the rest of the page. Shadow DOM Structure Document └── BODY └── custom-button └── Shadow Root └── BUTTON The button exists inside its own isolated DOM tree.
